1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,400
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:02,767
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,553 --> 00:00:07,320
This photo...

4
00:00:08,771 --> 00:00:11,400
Yes. It's an estimated face...

5
00:00:11,967 --> 00:00:15,067
based on the photo inside the necklace
and a current photo of Madam.

6
00:00:30,429 --> 00:00:32,888
How accurate is this photo?

7
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,567
Around 60 percent, they say.

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:37,767
We're cross-checking it
with facial recognition algorithms...

9
00:00:37,967 --> 00:00:41,400
against local missing women databases,
overseas adoptee communities,

10
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:44,067
and public social media photos.

11
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,367
At around 60 percent,

12
00:00:47,967 --> 00:00:51,300
we can't place too much hope
on this alone.

13
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:54,491
So we're starting from the very beginning
and working backward.

14
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:56,767
We're reviewing orphanage records...

15
00:00:57,467 --> 00:00:59,400
from before her adoption in France,
and tracing where she went...

16
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:02,267
after being placed with a foster family...

17
00:01:02,267 --> 00:01:05,491
as well as which facility she entered
after returning to Korea.

18
00:01:06,367 --> 00:01:08,872
We're also looking into
how basic information...

19
00:01:08,872 --> 00:01:10,767
like her name and age
disappeared during that process.

20
00:01:11,767 --> 00:01:16,067
I can't imagine
how hard her life must've been.

21
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:21,467
And we've re-registered Madam's DNA
in the database,

22
00:01:22,367 --> 00:01:24,219
but since there are no matching records,

23
00:01:25,224 --> 00:01:27,467
it seems her daughter
never registered hers.

24
00:01:28,859 --> 00:01:32,600
If she had,
we would've found her long ago.

25
00:01:34,467 --> 00:01:35,683
Like I said before,

26
00:01:36,419 --> 00:01:39,600
this must never get out.

27
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:43,867
Yes. CEO Ko seems
to have caught on to something, though.

28
00:01:44,127 --> 00:01:45,127
I know.

29
00:01:46,422 --> 00:01:48,155
Leave CEO Ko to me.

30
00:01:49,667 --> 00:01:51,267
I'm counting on you.

31
00:02:11,967 --> 00:02:14,367
(Eldest Daughter)

32
00:02:17,235 --> 00:02:20,767
What? Calling to check
whether your mom's dead or alive?

33
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:24,067
No way.
I was just wondering if you slept well.

34
00:02:24,767 --> 00:02:27,600
How was the hotel bed?
Did you eat breakfast?

35
00:02:28,067 --> 00:02:32,293
Yeah, it was so soft I slept like a baby.

36
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:34,808
And I stuffed myself with whatever
that breakfast thing was too.

37
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:38,192
That's good, Mom. Where are you now?

38
00:02:38,567 --> 00:02:39,567
Where?

39
00:02:40,973 --> 00:02:44,323
I'm drinking coffee
at the hotel caféoverlooking the river.

40
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:46,167
That's so cool, Mom.

41
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,500
I put some money in your bank account.

42
00:02:48,867 --> 00:02:50,600
Eat the finest meals...

43
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:53,067
and go shopping at a department store too,
okay?

44
00:02:54,367 --> 00:02:56,200
I run away once and hit the jackpot.

45
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:59,531
If I'd known this would happen,
I would've run away more often.

46
00:03:00,667 --> 00:03:03,088
Hang up now. You're probably at work.

47
00:03:03,667 --> 00:03:07,304
Mom,
when are you thinking of coming home...

48
00:03:07,967 --> 00:03:11,013
I'm finally taking a solo trip for once.
Are you a baby?

49
00:03:12,043 --> 00:03:14,160
It's not like you keep crying for food.

50
00:03:14,567 --> 00:03:15,728
Fine, okay.

51
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:18,967
You just have to keep answering your phone
like this, all right?

52
00:03:20,155 --> 00:03:21,300
Mom.

53
00:03:21,947 --> 00:03:24,221
If you could just call Dad once...

54
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,400
I'm hanging up.

55
00:03:29,884 --> 00:03:30,884
Mom...

56
00:03:32,805 --> 00:03:34,392
Can't she just forgive Dad already?

57
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,376
Yeah, it's me. Come meet me.

58
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:01,019
And don't tell anyone.

59
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:11,167
Should I go out
and buy some energy drinks or something?

60
00:04:16,267 --> 00:04:18,567
Sorry. You're tired, right?

61
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,701
We should've finished earlier last night.

62
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,100
What if someone hears you say that?

63
00:04:24,077 --> 00:04:26,925
Let me correct that.
It wasn't night, it was until dawn.

64
00:04:27,067 --> 00:04:28,367
Seriously.

65
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:31,667
Should I go buy some energy drinks
or something?

66
00:04:32,256 --> 00:04:34,021
You've been yawning nonstop too.

67
00:04:34,267 --> 00:04:36,367
I'm worried people might get
the wrong idea again.

68
00:04:36,367 --> 00:04:39,467
Seriously,
it's not like we did anything wrong.

69
00:04:39,667 --> 00:04:42,744
It's not a crime to rehearse...

70
00:04:42,744 --> 00:04:44,616
to prepare hard for the presentation.

71
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,237
Team Manager, you were here too?

72
00:04:49,579 --> 00:04:52,741
Yes, I needed some caffeine.
I'll get going then.

73
00:04:58,067 --> 00:04:59,731
Is something going on at home these days?

74
00:05:00,323 --> 00:05:02,000
You seemed
to have left work early yesterday too.

75
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:05,779
Yes. Things have been a bit chaotic
at home lately.

76
00:05:07,027 --> 00:05:09,194
Every family goes through things.

77
00:05:10,517 --> 00:05:13,115
I have a suggestion for you,
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

78
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:16,567
Our company has
an overseas training program...

79
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:18,091
for new employees.

80
00:05:18,446 --> 00:05:19,446
Overseas training?

81
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:22,767
Yes. It's a six-month short-term program,

82
00:05:22,767 --> 00:05:24,141
and the competition is fierce every year.

83
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,576
You're an intern,

84
00:05:26,675 --> 00:05:28,567
but I can write you
a recommendation letter.

85
00:05:28,567 --> 00:05:29,741
Would you like to apply?

86
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:32,168
That really sounds like
a great opportunity.

87
00:05:33,515 --> 00:05:36,867
But right now, we're in the middle
of the retirement community competition.

88
00:05:36,967 --> 00:05:39,243
Just because you apply
doesn't mean you'll get in.

89
00:05:39,467 --> 00:05:41,429
It takes a month or two
for the results to come out.

90
00:05:42,027 --> 00:05:43,967
If you get selected,
you could coordinate...

91
00:05:43,967 --> 00:05:46,507
your departure schedule with the company.
What do you think?

92
00:05:47,667 --> 00:05:50,477
It's truly more than I deserve,

93
00:05:51,045 --> 00:05:54,067
but the second round of the competition
is when Joy's development begins,

94
00:05:54,531 --> 00:05:56,411
so I want to focus only on that.

95
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:59,723
Well, if that's how you feel,
there's nothing I can do.

96
00:06:00,367 --> 00:06:03,117
For now, I'll send you
the training program materials by email.

97
00:06:03,567 --> 00:06:05,960
Take a look,
and if you change your mind, let me know.

98
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:09,267
Okay, thank you. I'll get back to work.

99
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:18,635
What exactly happened?

100
00:06:19,229 --> 00:06:22,155
I only found out this morning
that you left home.

101
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:26,083
You didn't tell Eun Hyeong
you were meeting me, right?

102
00:06:26,667 --> 00:06:29,344
No. You told me not to tell anyone.

103
00:06:32,688 --> 00:06:36,624
I think I've been selfish...

104
00:06:37,842 --> 00:06:38,842
toward you.

105
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,600
Sorry?

106
00:06:42,115 --> 00:06:43,115
Because my son...

107
00:06:44,277 --> 00:06:46,336
is kind and upright,

108
00:06:47,067 --> 00:06:50,397
I think I expected you
to endure everything no matter what.

109
00:06:51,659 --> 00:06:53,877
Well, from your perspective as a mom,
that's only natural.

110
00:06:54,567 --> 00:06:56,944
What mother-in-law wouldn't try
to stop her daughter-in-law...

111
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:59,499
from divorcing with a child involved?

112
00:07:00,251 --> 00:07:02,467
There's nothing in this world
that's truly natural.

113
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:05,267
Blood runs thicker than water.

114
00:07:06,024 --> 00:07:08,267
I only thought about things
from my son's side.

115
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:13,667
It's only been one night
since I left home,

116
00:07:15,267 --> 00:07:17,067
but all kinds of thoughts
have been running through my mind.

117
00:07:19,549 --> 00:07:22,717
"What have I been living for
all this time?"

118
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:24,867
"Who have I been living for?"

119
00:07:26,471 --> 00:07:30,171
I thought my family was my entire world,

120
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:36,445
but while doing that,
I never truly lived my own life.

121
00:07:39,987 --> 00:07:41,603
So, Ji Seon...

122
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:46,213
You should get divorced.

123
00:07:47,269 --> 00:07:49,967
Sorry? Divorce?

124
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:52,419
You endure it because he's a good husband.

125
00:07:53,024 --> 00:07:55,524
You endure it because you have a child
you love more than life itself.

126
00:07:57,500 --> 00:08:01,400
And if you keep enduring like that,
time will pass somehow, but...

127
00:08:02,883 --> 00:08:03,883
Later,

128
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,224
much later...

129
00:08:07,603 --> 00:08:09,067
you can't end up like me,

130
00:08:09,672 --> 00:08:11,941
with nothing left of your own life.

131
00:08:15,667 --> 00:08:18,120
Do whatever you want to do.

132
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:21,573
Why are you saying that?

133
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:24,000
We've decided to try again.

134
00:08:24,632 --> 00:08:27,427
Some things can be fixed with effort,
and some things can't.

135
00:08:28,713 --> 00:08:29,744
Eun Hyeong...

136
00:08:31,667 --> 00:08:33,367
He's just like his father,

137
00:08:34,269 --> 00:08:37,967
so he may never really change
for the rest of his life.

138
00:08:39,696 --> 00:08:42,597
And if you're worried because of Bit Na,
don't be.

139
00:08:42,949 --> 00:08:45,867
You can still be a mother after a divorce.

140
00:08:47,016 --> 00:08:48,167
No matter who raises her,

141
00:08:48,732 --> 00:08:51,765
you both just need to fulfill
your roles as parents.

142
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,120
Mother...

143
00:08:53,438 --> 00:08:55,238
I've said everything I needed to say,
so let's get up now.

144
00:08:55,467 --> 00:08:58,061
Mother,
would you like to come to our house?

145
00:08:58,667 --> 00:09:00,467
- Your house?
- Yes.

146
00:09:00,467 --> 00:09:02,267
Stay in Bit Na's room for a few days,

147
00:09:02,867 --> 00:09:04,667
and once you've calmed down...

148
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:07,167
I'm grateful for the thought, but no.

149
00:09:07,851 --> 00:09:11,283
More than anything else,
put yourself first...

150
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:14,367
and think carefully about it, okay?

151
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:33,080
Just what kind of work is he handling
for the Chairman to be busy day and night?

152
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,755
What even requires security this airtight?

153
00:09:46,507 --> 00:09:47,967
What brings you here?

154
00:09:48,767 --> 00:09:51,500
Why? You come to our house all the time.

155
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:52,667
I can't come to yours?

156
00:09:53,835 --> 00:09:55,261
No, it's not that.

157
00:09:55,767 --> 00:09:57,400
I was just surprised.

158
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,400
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

159
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:02,267
Your house is so cozy. I like it.

160
00:10:02,267 --> 00:10:03,797
Let's see, how many rooms are there?

161
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:06,767
It's not even her first time here.
What's with her?

162
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,067
This must be the master bedroom,

163
00:10:09,367 --> 00:10:11,667
and that's Seung Ri's room?
Seung Wu's room?

164
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:14,367
Yes.

165
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,500
There's another room over there.
What's that?

166
00:10:17,267 --> 00:10:18,567
Seung Ri's dad's study.

167
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:20,672
I see.

168
00:10:21,456 --> 00:10:25,067
Right, I'm starving right now.

169
00:10:25,067 --> 00:10:25,859
Make me something to eat.

170
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:28,267
- What?
- I skipped lunch...

171
00:10:28,267 --> 00:10:30,509
because I was dieting,
and I'm suddenly starving.

172
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,167
I'm going to wash my hands
in the bathroom,

173
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,421
so set the table for me.

174
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,096
Why is she suddenly asking for food
at my house?

175
00:10:37,976 --> 00:10:40,493
Okay,
but don't expect too many side dishes.

176
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,547
Thanks!

177
00:10:56,967 --> 00:10:59,167
Seriously, so meticulous.

178
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:02,029
Now, where does he usually hide keys?

179
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,000
What are you doing?

180
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:12,800
You startled me.

181
00:11:13,427 --> 00:11:14,567
Mrs. Ko.

182
00:11:15,995 --> 00:11:18,333
Seung Wu, what are you doing here?

183
00:11:18,611 --> 00:11:22,367
It looked like you were searching
for something, so I thought I'd help.

184
00:11:24,467 --> 00:11:25,667
Should I call your assistant for you?

185
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:28,608
- Mom!
- Hey!

186
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:30,367
Your mom is my assistant?

187
00:11:30,567 --> 00:11:33,067
We're besties, okay?

188
00:11:34,283 --> 00:11:36,700
I was trying to find the bathroom
and came into the wrong room.

189
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:37,900
Where's the bathroom?

190
00:11:38,755 --> 00:11:40,200
Across from here.

191
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,867
Really? Okay, thanks.

192
00:11:44,952 --> 00:11:48,395
By the way, Seung Wu,
are you still unemployed?

193
00:11:48,667 --> 00:11:49,667
Excuse me?

194
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,200
Here, this is your allowance.

195
00:11:55,697 --> 00:11:57,997
And keep my coming into this room today...

196
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,285
a secret from your mom and dad.

197
00:12:01,739 --> 00:12:04,299
I'm not that clueless.

198
00:12:04,299 --> 00:12:08,100
Seung Wu, you really grew up well.

199
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:10,900
You're handsome
and have great fashion sense too.

200
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:12,667
Totally my type.

201
00:12:13,267 --> 00:12:14,800
See you. Yeah.

202
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,167
Bye.

203
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:22,667
That lady's always so mysterious.

204
00:12:29,327 --> 00:12:30,327
Hello, Producer.

205
00:12:31,899 --> 00:12:35,005
What? She opened my webtoon email?

206
00:12:36,571 --> 00:12:39,536
Then that means she did read it.

207
00:12:40,629 --> 00:12:44,700
Producer,
could I get the writer's phone number?

208
00:12:47,328 --> 00:12:48,811
Of course, I understand...

209
00:12:48,811 --> 00:12:51,203
that personal information
is a sensitive issue these days, but...

210
00:12:51,714 --> 00:12:53,514
Please?

211
00:12:54,357 --> 00:12:56,099
Yes, I did read it.

212
00:12:57,576 --> 00:13:01,408
It's not bad, but collaborating
with that man is a little...

213
00:13:02,511 --> 00:13:03,844
What? My number?

214
00:13:05,629 --> 00:13:06,867
Anyway, okay.

215
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:10,067
I'll think about it a bit more. Bye.

216
00:13:21,736 --> 00:13:25,360
You're the writer of "The ER Witch,"
Doro Dorothy, right?

217
00:13:25,597 --> 00:13:28,101
Yes, I am. And who are you?

218
00:13:29,167 --> 00:13:32,096
I'm the Napkin... No, "The ER Witch"...

219
00:13:33,327 --> 00:13:34,327
No, I mean...

220
00:13:34,877 --> 00:13:39,100
I'm Seo Seung Wu,
the writer of "Secretary by Nature."

221
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:42,840
Just get to the point. I'm busy.

222
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:44,067
Writer...

223
00:13:44,967 --> 00:13:46,600
Please meet me just once.

224
00:13:47,067 --> 00:13:48,267
This is my last request.

225
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:50,800
What? Your last request?

226
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:56,667
I'll never bother you again,
so please, just this once.

227
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:04,467
(CSAT)

228
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:10,267
(CSAT Math Section
Past Exam Questions Complete Review)

229
00:14:13,967 --> 00:14:15,967
(Differentiation of Various Functions,
Various Differentiation Methods)

230
00:14:15,967 --> 00:14:16,967
Differentiation and integration?

231
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:22,149
I barely even remember factoring.

232
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:37,067
(CSAT Prep Books for 2027 Now Available)

233
00:14:47,749 --> 00:14:49,621
- This is the brochure for external use.
- Okay.

234
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:52,328
Did you pull another all-nighter
at the office yesterday?

235
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:54,667
No, I left around 10 p.m. Why?

236
00:14:54,805 --> 00:14:56,767
You've been yawning nonstop since earlier.

237
00:15:02,867 --> 00:15:04,848
Must be spring fatigue.

238
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:08,280
I think this should be enough.

239
00:15:08,567 --> 00:15:09,867
- Okay, got it.
- Okay.

240
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:16,229
All right, tomorrow is finally D-Day.

241
00:15:16,811 --> 00:15:18,352
The long-awaited first competition round.

242
00:15:19,339 --> 00:15:21,392
Both teams have done their best,

243
00:15:21,567 --> 00:15:23,771
so how about we all have dinner
after tomorrow's competition?

244
00:15:23,867 --> 00:15:24,867
Sounds good.

245
00:15:26,767 --> 00:15:28,088
All right, let's keep it up until the end.

246
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:43,867
Team Two, gather in the meeting room.

247
00:15:43,867 --> 00:15:44,900
Let's do the final rehearsal.

248
00:15:46,667 --> 00:15:48,567
Yes, we should do it again.

249
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:50,400
Of course we should.

250
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:58,467
Don't you think Team Manager Ko
has changed a lot lately?

251
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,967
At first, he was completely laid-back.

252
00:16:01,167 --> 00:16:03,320
In short, he's kind of two-faced.

253
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:05,867
Hypocritical to the core.

254
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:09,367
Mr. Han Ji Hun, have you finished
the final check on the PPT materials?

255
00:16:09,525 --> 00:16:12,767
Yes.
I'll go over everything one last time.

256
00:16:19,267 --> 00:16:21,467
Mr. Kim, go to the archive room...

257
00:16:21,467 --> 00:16:24,512
and copy the retirement community
benchmarking report...

258
00:16:24,512 --> 00:16:26,379
and blueprints
Kangsu Construction prepared...

259
00:16:26,797 --> 00:16:28,133
before our TF team was formed.

260
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,867
Why do we need them now?

261
00:16:31,224 --> 00:16:33,232
It's to make sure
not a single thing overlaps.

262
00:16:33,232 --> 00:16:34,567
Not even the smallest detail.

263
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:36,952
- Okay, understood.
- Wait.

264
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:40,400
You can't miss even one thing.

265
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:43,467
Take your time and be extremely thorough.

266
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:45,200
Yes.

267
00:16:46,277 --> 00:16:47,567
What should I do?

268
00:16:47,883 --> 00:16:50,100
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, would you please sit here?

269
00:16:50,661 --> 00:16:52,767
I think the distance between there...

270
00:16:52,767 --> 00:16:54,453
and the presenter and judges' seats
is perfect.

271
00:16:57,256 --> 00:16:58,560
Here?

272
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:01,035
Perfect. Okay.

273
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:04,867
Shoot, I left something at the office.

274
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,800
Just sit here and wait a bit.

275
00:17:06,967 --> 00:17:09,700
Stretch your legs
and sit as comfortably as possible, okay?

276
00:17:14,163 --> 00:17:15,163
What is this?

277
00:17:35,449 --> 00:17:36,449
What are you doing here?

278
00:17:37,235 --> 00:17:38,900
We were rehearsing,

279
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:40,576
and I got tired, so I was stretching.

280
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:42,440
Stretching...

281
00:17:44,167 --> 00:17:47,472
You know the opposing team's strategy
is top secret, right?

282
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,567
Ko Gyeol, take it easy already.

283
00:18:04,851 --> 00:18:07,067
So did you submit your resignation?

284
00:18:07,367 --> 00:18:10,800
Yeah. My replacement comes tomorrow,
so after I hand everything off,

285
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:12,867
I'll officially start next week.

286
00:18:14,173 --> 00:18:17,251
I mean, it's just cleaning.
Do you really need a handoff?

287
00:18:18,864 --> 00:18:22,067
I want to know
what exactly my duties will be.

288
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:26,067
Well, since you're my assistant,
you're basically doing everything with me.

289
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:29,200
Starting with driving,
accompanying me to and from work,

290
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:31,567
managing schedules, and meetings too.

291
00:18:32,067 --> 00:18:34,731
So in short, you can think of yourself
as my shadow.

292
00:18:35,443 --> 00:18:38,067
Like gum, stuck right to me.

293
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:42,872
Right,
and once I become the next chairman,

294
00:18:43,067 --> 00:18:46,053
your position and duties will change too,
so don't worry too much.

295
00:18:47,939 --> 00:18:50,500
Hey, and I'm only telling you this.

296
00:18:51,267 --> 00:18:54,267
Seo Gwon Sik is completely finished now,
so you...

297
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:55,267
Got it.

298
00:18:57,343 --> 00:18:59,076
I'll start working
at the secretary's office next week.

299
00:18:59,315 --> 00:19:00,501
Wait. I almost forgot.

300
00:19:01,437 --> 00:19:04,867
From now on,
the way you address me has to change too.

301
00:19:07,531 --> 00:19:12,633
I'd love to keep talking comfortably
with you like we do now,

302
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:14,467
but that's not how companies work.

303
00:19:14,467 --> 00:19:15,533
People are watching.

304
00:19:19,367 --> 00:19:23,000
Yes, understood, sir.

305
00:19:31,096 --> 00:19:34,144
The great Cho Seong Jun himself
said to me,

306
00:19:35,005 --> 00:19:36,200
"Yes, understood, sir."

307
00:19:36,767 --> 00:19:38,059
This is driving me crazy. I love it.

308
00:19:40,267 --> 00:19:42,200
(Checking Account, Kang Yeon Ja)

309
00:20:02,222 --> 00:20:03,222
What are you doing, Dad?

310
00:20:04,267 --> 00:20:05,367
Nothing.

311
00:20:06,267 --> 00:20:08,267
Eun Ae, starting next week,

312
00:20:09,211 --> 00:20:11,467
I'll be working
as CEO Ko Dae Chi's assistant.

313
00:20:11,767 --> 00:20:12,767
What?

314
00:20:13,767 --> 00:20:16,267
Are you sure you'll be okay
working for your friend?

315
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:21,000
It's less physically demanding,
and the pay is better too.

316
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:23,549
I've decided to just think positively
about it.

317
00:20:24,627 --> 00:20:25,727
Congratulations, Dad.

318
00:20:26,661 --> 00:20:30,067
I talked to Mom earlier today,
and she says she's doing well.

319
00:20:30,630 --> 00:20:31,630
Okay, got it.

320
00:20:32,167 --> 00:20:33,728
Go upstairs and rest. You must be tired.

321
00:20:33,824 --> 00:20:35,400
I'm going to stop by Cho Rong's house.

322
00:20:35,701 --> 00:20:37,567
I should update Grandma about Mom too.

323
00:20:38,227 --> 00:20:39,227
Sleep well.

324
00:20:39,567 --> 00:20:41,336
Okay, go ahead.

325
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:03,900
(To my beloved wife Yeon Ja)

326
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:07,500
- What? You met Mom?
- Yeah.

327
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:10,800
Honey, why didn't you tell me?

328
00:21:11,100 --> 00:21:12,523
I should've gone with you.

329
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:16,155
Mother told me not to tell anyone
no matter what.

330
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:18,381
I talked to Grandma on the phone too,

331
00:21:18,936 --> 00:21:20,367
and Grandma said she misses me.

332
00:21:20,567 --> 00:21:23,032
What? You talked to Grandma too?

333
00:21:23,229 --> 00:21:26,667
Yeah. I told Grandma
her braised beef was delicious,

334
00:21:26,667 --> 00:21:28,504
and Grandma said
she'd make her more tasty food next time.

335
00:21:29,853 --> 00:21:32,235
If she said that to Bit Na,

336
00:21:32,767 --> 00:21:34,100
maybe she'll come back soon.

337
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:36,773
The feeling I got was...

338
00:21:37,152 --> 00:21:40,085
that she'd let go of everything.

339
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,243
What do you mean by that?

340
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,467
Well...

341
00:21:44,976 --> 00:21:46,891
It's a little hard to say to you.

342
00:21:48,367 --> 00:21:51,536
Should I just go tell Father everything?

343
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:55,811
I think Father may need
to go look for Mother himself.

344
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:57,100
Wait.

345
00:21:58,003 --> 00:22:00,900
If Father steps in, it could backfire.

346
00:22:01,967 --> 00:22:04,437
But we can't just sit around
and wait forever either.

347
00:22:07,277 --> 00:22:09,167
To tell him or not to tell him...

348
00:22:10,167 --> 00:22:11,864
This really is a dilemma.

349
00:22:12,067 --> 00:22:14,133
What should I do?

350
00:22:14,317 --> 00:22:16,700
So when do you think she'll come back?

351
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:18,567
I'm not really sure.

352
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:22,367
She said this was her first solo trip ever
and told us not to bother her.

353
00:22:22,611 --> 00:22:24,981
She must've really reached her limit.

354
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:28,200
Her world seemed to already be collapsing
when it was just you kids causing trouble.

355
00:22:28,567 --> 00:22:30,467
How could your father
do that to your mother...

356
00:22:30,584 --> 00:22:31,888
Grandma.

357
00:22:32,216 --> 00:22:34,795
You think Eun Ae's father hid it
because he wanted to?

358
00:22:34,795 --> 00:22:38,533
Even so,
whether it was shameful or miserable,

359
00:22:38,767 --> 00:22:41,611
if he'd just been honest from the start,

360
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:43,965
would things have turned into such a mess?

361
00:22:44,723 --> 00:22:46,200
Grandma, hurry inside and get some sleep.

362
00:22:46,267 --> 00:22:47,700
I'll clean up the rest.

363
00:22:47,767 --> 00:22:50,536
Yeah. This hour is the death of me.

364
00:22:51,367 --> 00:22:53,667
You kids wrap it up too and head home,
all right?

365
00:22:53,967 --> 00:22:57,367
Yes. I have a big thing at work tomorrow,
so I should go home early.

366
00:22:57,667 --> 00:22:59,667
- Good night.
- Okay.

367
00:23:03,567 --> 00:23:05,167
What's so important at work tomorrow?

368
00:23:05,167 --> 00:23:07,245
Remember I told you about the competition
at the company?

369
00:23:08,267 --> 00:23:09,267
That's tomorrow?

370
00:23:09,567 --> 00:23:12,967
But with everything going on at home,
haven't you been distracted at work?

371
00:23:12,967 --> 00:23:13,967
Exactly.

372
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:17,597
Thankfully,
Team Manager has been very understanding.

373
00:23:19,367 --> 00:23:23,387
He looks so cold-hearted,
but he was understanding?

374
00:23:33,367 --> 00:23:35,000
Don't worry about anything and go.

375
00:23:36,467 --> 00:23:37,467
What are you doing here?

376
00:23:38,067 --> 00:23:40,300
We were rehearsing, and I got tired,
so I was stretching.

377
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:47,467
What? Did he suggest the rehearsal
on purpose so I could sleep?

378
00:23:48,608 --> 00:23:51,367
What are you trying to say?

379
00:23:52,688 --> 00:23:56,467
Look at your face turning red.
What's this?

380
00:23:57,867 --> 00:23:59,067
Seriously, I'm leaving.

381
00:24:01,667 --> 00:24:05,000
That girl.
If you like him, just say you like him.

382
00:24:06,767 --> 00:24:09,008
Looks like spring is finally coming
for Eun Ae.

383
00:24:15,567 --> 00:24:18,500
How did he know my shoelace came undone?

384
00:24:20,613 --> 00:24:21,700
What am I even thinking?

385
00:24:30,235 --> 00:24:32,767
Maid, what is this?

386
00:24:32,767 --> 00:24:34,403
Do you know what day today is?

387
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:37,900
You want Min Ho to slip and slide...

388
00:24:38,148 --> 00:24:39,815
out of the competition...

389
00:24:40,100 --> 00:24:42,048
after eating this slippery seaweed soup
or what?

390
00:24:42,216 --> 00:24:43,216
What?

391
00:24:44,291 --> 00:24:46,112
I made the seaweed soup.

392
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:48,267
It's fine, so go do your work.

393
00:24:48,267 --> 00:24:49,379
Yes, Madam.

394
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:53,859
Mother, why today of all days...

395
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:55,167
What's today?

396
00:24:56,293 --> 00:24:59,595
Father has been saying
he wants some refreshing seaweed soup,

397
00:24:59,595 --> 00:25:01,367
so I made it.

398
00:25:01,822 --> 00:25:02,822
Father has?

399
00:25:02,822 --> 00:25:06,500
We always eat seaweed and oyster soup
around this time every year.

400
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:09,899
That's true,
but seaweed is kind of slippery.

401
00:25:10,143 --> 00:25:11,243
And today of all days...

402
00:25:11,767 --> 00:25:13,367
All right, everyone, eat up.

403
00:25:13,667 --> 00:25:15,767
Yes, Father. Enjoy your meal.

404
00:25:16,712 --> 00:25:19,467
So slippery and slick.
This is some rich soup, seriously.

405
00:25:20,367 --> 00:25:22,267
- Did you sleep well?
- Yeah, come sit down.

406
00:25:25,419 --> 00:25:27,067
Why are you taking my soup?

407
00:25:27,813 --> 00:25:29,315
You can just eat plain rice.

408
00:25:29,867 --> 00:25:31,000
Seriously, Su Jeong.

409
00:25:31,667 --> 00:25:34,167
Is Min Ho a student taking the CSAT?

410
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:37,509
Still, you shouldn't ignore jinxes.

411
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,997
Please understand, Father.

412
00:25:42,246 --> 00:25:43,546
Did you prepare well?

413
00:25:44,267 --> 00:25:46,400
Yes, Grandpa. I did my best.

414
00:25:46,567 --> 00:25:48,567
Good. I'll look forward to it.

415
00:25:49,667 --> 00:25:51,300
Did Gyeol leave first?

416
00:25:52,008 --> 00:25:53,893
Yes. Before he left,

417
00:25:53,893 --> 00:25:56,667
he had a quick breakfast, so don't worry.

418
00:25:57,800 --> 00:25:58,800
That kid, honestly.

419
00:25:58,867 --> 00:26:02,157
Would it kill him to eat with everyone
and go to work together?

420
00:26:02,432 --> 00:26:03,699
He's making it way too obvious.

421
00:26:04,997 --> 00:26:06,700
Obvious? What's obvious?

422
00:26:07,653 --> 00:26:09,149
Father, come on.

423
00:26:09,700 --> 00:26:11,469
It's not like
we're making him feel unwelcome.

424
00:26:11,469 --> 00:26:12,837
And from other people's perspective too,

425
00:26:13,107 --> 00:26:15,907
he acts like it's all our fault
he can't blend in with the family.

426
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:18,800
Father,

427
00:26:19,367 --> 00:26:21,605
couldn't you make me a judge too?

428
00:26:22,651 --> 00:26:24,667
What? A judge?

429
00:26:24,967 --> 00:26:28,667
I'm also a major shareholder,
so I figured I'm qualified.

430
00:26:28,667 --> 00:26:30,160
If you'd just let me...

431
00:26:31,867 --> 00:26:33,336
Well, honey.

432
00:26:33,621 --> 00:26:35,567
This crystal cup is so transparent...

433
00:26:35,567 --> 00:26:37,941
I can practically see through it,
and it's making me uncomfortable.

434
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:40,120
Could you switch it with a ceramic cup?

435
00:26:40,652 --> 00:26:41,652
What?

436
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:55,549
Joy, it's finally D-Day.

437
00:26:56,067 --> 00:26:57,567
Our team can do this, right?

438
00:26:57,667 --> 00:27:00,499
Based on objective data analysis,
the probability of success is...

439
00:27:00,867 --> 00:27:04,900
approximately 66.6 percent.

440
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:07,867
What? Why is the probability so low?

441
00:27:08,067 --> 00:27:10,576
Based on analysis
of Team Manager Ko Gyeol's rehearsals,

442
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:13,767
when he gets flustered,
he talks fast and stumbles.

443
00:27:13,967 --> 00:27:17,867
If he can control his heart rate
in front of you...

444
00:27:17,867 --> 00:27:19,800
and remain calm,

445
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:21,967
the odds of victory will increase.

446
00:27:22,367 --> 00:27:25,597
What? What are you talking about?

447
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:28,100
Good luck.

448
00:27:28,900 --> 00:27:31,500
You've gotten really smart lately,
haven't you?

449
00:27:32,867 --> 00:27:33,967
Anyway, I'm heading out.

450
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:41,467
Wish me luck.

451
00:27:52,067 --> 00:27:53,100
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

452
00:27:54,167 --> 00:27:55,389
Team Manager.

453
00:28:24,167 --> 00:28:25,567
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
